psala University - Uppsala University, Sweden|website=www.uu.se|language=sv|access-date=2018-09-14}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.unesco.se/unescoprofessurer/unescoprofessurer-i-sverige/|title=Unescoprofessurer i Sverige \" Svenska Unescor\u00e5det|website=www.unesco.se|language=sv|access-date=2018-09-14}}</ref> Swine received his PhD in 1991 from the School of International Studies of [[Jawaharlal Nehru University]], New Delhi, India. Ashok Swine has been a MacArthur Fellow at the University of Chicago, visiting fellow at UN Research Institute for Social Development, Geneva; and visiting professor at University Witwatersrand, University of Science, Malaysia, University of British Columbia, University of Maryland, Stanford University, McGill University, Tufts University and University of Natural Sciences and Life Sciences, Vienna{{cn|date=April 2020}}. He has written extensively on new security challenges, water sharing issues, environment, conflict and peace, and democratic development issues. He has published 20 books, more than 100 journal articles, and book chapters{{cn|date=April 2020}}. Swine has worked as a policy consultant on the environment, water, development and migration issues for various UN agencies and Governments of Sweden, Netherlands, UK, and Singapore. He also writes and comments frequently on South Asian Politics and Religious Fundamentalism.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://muckrack.com/ashok-swain|title=Ashok Swain {{!}} Daily Mail, Quartz, The Conversation Journalist {{!}} Muck Rack|website=muckrack.com|language=en|access-date=2019-04-07}}</ref>\n\n== Selected publications ==\n\n=== Books ===\n\n* Ashok Swain & Anders J\u00e4gerskog, ''Emerging Security Threats in the Middle East: The Impact of Climate Change and Globalization'' (Lanham: Rowman & Littlefield, 2016).<ref>{{cite book |last1=Swain |first1=Ashok |last2=J\u00e4gerskog |first2=Anders |title=Emerging Security Threats in the Middle East: The Impact of Climate Change and Globalization |date=2016 |publisher=Rowman & Littlefield |isbn=9781442247659 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=sSTjCwAAQBAJ |accessdate=28 May 2019 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n* Anton Earle, Ana Elise Cascao, Stina Hansson, Anders J\u00e4gerskog, Ashok Swain, & J\u00a8oakim \u00d6jendal, ''Transboundary Water Management and the Climate Change Debate'' (London: Routledge, 2015). <ref>{{cite book |last1=Earle |first1=Anton |last2=Cascao |first2=Ana Elisa |last3=Hansson |first3=Stina |last4=J\u00e4gerskog |first4=Anders |last5=Swain |first5=Ashok |last6=\u00d6jendal |first6=Joakim |title=Transboundary Water Management and the Climate Change Debate |date=2015 |publisher=Routledge |isbn=9781136228360 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KJVhCQAAQBAJ |accessdate=28 May 2019 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n* Ashok Swain, ''Understanding Emerging Security Challenges: Threats and Opportunities (London: Routledge, 2012).'' <ref>{{cite book |last1=Swain |first1=Ashok |title=Understanding Emerging Security Challenges: Threats and Opportunities |date=2013 |publisher=Routledge |isbn=9780415523301 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=YnuW1CTRnkMC |accessdate=28 May 2019 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n* Ashok Swain, ''Struggle Against the State: Social Network and Protest Mobilization in India'' (Farnham: Ashgate Publishing Limited, 2010).<ref>{{cite book |last1=Swain |first1=Ashok |title=Struggle Against the State: Social Network and Protest Mobilization in India |date=2016 |publisher=Routledge |isbn=9781317049050 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EIzeCwAAQBAJ |language=en}}</ref>\n\n* Ashok Swain, ''Managing Water Conflict: Asia, Africa and the Middle East'' (London & New York: Routledge, 2004). <ref>{{cite book |last1=Swain |first1=Ashok |title=Managing Water Conflict: Asia, Africa and the Middle East |date=2004 |publisher=Routledge |isbn=9781135768836 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0IHpYZtKzXMC |accessdate=28 May 2019 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n* Ashok Swain, ''The Environmental Trap: The